channel.title: Frame Error caused by Server?
channel.description:
[code]# # A fatal error has been detected by the Java Runtime Environment: # # EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION (0xc0000005) at pc=0x000000006d84a566, pid=8132, t id=6368 # # JRE version: 6.0_18-b07 # Java VM: Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (16.0-b13 mixed mode windows-amd64 ) # Problematic frame: # V [jvm.dll+0x5a566] # # An error report file with more information is saved as: # H:\RS\MoparScape\hs_err_pid8132.log # # If you would like to submit a bug report, please visit: # http://java.sun.com/webapps/bugreport/crash.jsp # Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
That's the CMD output... I don't know whats wrong never encountered this error before! When I click on the stairs in Lumbridge leading up to the castle or click past them to go up or down,It crashes,Its not the client tryed to see what would happen with two Different Clients! My own Custom one and Moparscape's one.
If anyone could point me to a Tutorial or a walk-though on what this means so I can learn about it,Or give me a hint on where to look to fix it that would be great! Thanks!
Code God Of Rs
